		  <style></style><div style="opacity:0" class="sc-eQxpLG kmqMaZ __pf __pf_ZJ7LS_X-" id="__pf"><div data-pf-type="Body" class="sc-dkYRCH hYpqjU pf-365_"><div data-pf-type="Layout" class="sc-fHeRUh ihgygX pf-366_"><div data-section-id="pf-c126" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-367_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-368_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-369_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-370_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-372_">Breastfeeding at work: a spotlight on World Breastfeeding Week</span></h1><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-373_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-374_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-375_"><i class="sc-fbyfCU cFdiHx pf-376_ pfa pfa-book-open-reader" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Rose Mabiza</h3><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-377_"><i class="sc-fbyfCU cFdiHx pf-378_ pfa pfa-calendar-days" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>02-08-2023</h3></div></div></div><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_07fd68da-c8c8-470a-a3ed-c6b5c8e71494.jpg?v=1690969014" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_07fd68da-c8c8-470a-a3ed-c6b5c8e71494.jpg?v=1690969014 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_07fd68da-c8c8-470a-a3ed-c6b5c8e71494_1000x.jpg?v=1690969014 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_07fd68da-c8c8-470a-a3ed-c6b5c8e71494_500x.jpg?v=1690969014 320w" width="1824" height="1216" alt="Breastfeeding at work a spotlight on World Breastfeeding Week - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Breastfeeding at work a spotlight on World Breastfeeding Week - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-379_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5d45" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-380_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-381_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-382_"><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-383_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-385_">World Breastfeeding Week (WBW), observed in the first week of August each year, is a significant global campaign supported by many organisations, including the World Health Organization (WHO), UNICEF and Ministries of Health. This year, the focus is on breastfeeding and work, aiming to advocate for essential maternity rights that enable women to balance their breastfeeding journey with their professional responsibilities. <br><br>The key theme revolves around the idea that women should not have to choose between breastfeeding their children and their work. In this blog, we explore the significance of World Breastfeeding Week, what the law in Great Britain has to say and how the workplace can focus on supporting breastfeeding mothers.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-386_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-388_">The Theme: Breastfeeding at Work</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Theme_Breastfeeding_at_Work-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969174" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Theme_Breastfeeding_at_Work-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969174 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Theme_Breastfeeding_at_Work-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690969174 320w" width="1974" height="1318" alt="The Theme Breastfeeding at Work - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The Theme Breastfeeding at Work - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-389_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-390_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-392_">This year's theme focuses on breastfeeding and work, aiming to advocate for essential maternity rights that support breastfeeding. These are urgent issues for ensuring women can breastfeed as long as they wish to do so: more than half a billion working women worldwide are not given essential maternity protections in national laws, and just 20% of countries require employers to provide paid breaks and facilities for breastfeeding or expressing milk.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-393_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-395_">The&nbsp;legal landscape in Great Britain</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Legal_Landscape_in_Great_Britain_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969355" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Legal_Landscape_in_Great_Britain_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969355 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_Legal_Landscape_in_Great_Britain_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690969355 320w" width="2080" height="1387" alt="The Legal Landscape in Great Britain - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The Legal Landscape in Great Britain - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-396_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-397_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-399_">In Great Britain, the law acknowledges the significance of supporting breastfeeding mothers in the workplace. Mothers have the right to decide the duration of their breastfeeding journey, and employers must respect and accommodate their choice. Before rejoining the workforce, a breastfeeding mother should provide written notification to her employer about her breastfeeding status, prompting the employer to conduct a specific risk assessment. Workplace regulations mandate employers to provide suitable facilities for pregnant and breastfeeding mothers to rest. <br><br>To promote good practices, the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) recommends that employers offer a private, healthy, and safe environment for expressing and storing breast milk, recognising that toilets are unsuitable for this purpose. By adhering to these guidelines, employers can create a supportive workplace environment, allowing breastfeeding mothers to nurture their infants while excelling in their professional roles.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-400_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-402_">Ways a workplace can support breastfeeding mothers</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Ways_a_workplace_can_support_breastfeeding_mothers_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969458" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Ways_a_workplace_can_support_breastfeeding_mothers_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690969458 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Ways_a_workplace_can_support_breastfeeding_mothers_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690969458 320w" width="2453" height="1637" alt="Ways a workplace can support breastfeeding mothers - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Ways a workplace can support breastfeeding mothers - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-403_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-404_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-406_">Employers can offer flexible return-to-work options, such as part-time hours or working from home. These are essential to enable mothers to ease back into their professional roles while continuing their breastfeeding journey. Flexibility not only supports women in maintaining their careers but also helps them nurture their bond with their children. Colleagues can also play a significant role in supporting breastfeeding mothers by being supportive of flexible work arrangements when women return to work.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-407_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-409_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690970064" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690970064 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Breastfeeding_at_work_a_spotlight_on_World_Breastfeeding_Week_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690970064 320w" width="1840" height="1228" alt="Breastfeeding at work: a spotlight on World Breastfeeding Week - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Breastfeeding at work: a spotlight on World Breastfeeding Week - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-410_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-411_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-413_">World Breastfeeding Week emphasises the significance of supporting breastfeeding mothers in the workplace. This year's theme advocates for essential maternity rights, enabling women to balance their breastfeeding journey with work responsibilities. In Great Britain, the law acknowledges the importance of accommodating breastfeeding mothers, with regulations ensuring suitable facilities and, we aspire for a world that also adopts these practices. <br><br>Supporting breastfeeding at work means investing in healthier communities and workforces. As we advocate for essential maternity rights, we at <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></i></a> also respect and support every woman's choices and circumstances in how they decide to feed their baby. By fostering a nurturing and inclusive environment, we can ensure that women are supported to make the best decisions for themselves and their families. </span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-414_ pf-r pf-r-eh pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-415_"><div data-pf-type="Slideshow" class="sc-furwcr jFnGOX pf-416_"><div data-id="slider-69684f10-6390-465d-85e7-37eefff35f07-all" class="pf-slider scrollfix"><div class="pf-slide"><div style="display:block" class="sc-fIITEw glyLTg pf-417_" data-pf-type="SlideshowSlide"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-418_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-419_"><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-GEbAx gWfVlz pf-420_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/nhscareerslogo-1671516106607.png?v=1671516190" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/nhscareerslogo-167151610660